{"word":"ἐπίσχω","slug":"ἐπίσχω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπίσχω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:strengthened'>strengthd.</a> for <a href='S:ἐπέχω'><el>ἐπέχω</el></a>,\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to hold</i> or <i>direct towards</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <el>τινί</el> against one, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to restrain, withhold, check</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, attic:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>to restrain from</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> <i>to leave off, stop, wait</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>; <a href='S:imperative mood'>imperat.</a> <el>ἔπισχε</el>, <i>hold</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}